featured_reviews.review_id: According `History of Tamil Nadu' authored by R. Aalalasundaram, Muhamed Yusuf Khan(Marudhanayagam) legs were burried in this majid. Muhamed Yusuf Khan was born a Hindu, acquired knowledge from a Christian and died as a Muslim. The hangmen chopped his body into four pieces and buried them at various places -- his head in Tiruchi, legs in Periyakulam, hands in Palayamkottai and body in Madurai.
